<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<taxonomicName LSID="0CF84C6D-3590-5713-9D32-CAF2CC432888" authority="(Lower, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Lower" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Cerura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerura melanoglypta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanoglypta">Cerura melanoglypta (Lower, 1905)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
One species in the 
<bibRefCitation author="Rajaei, Hossein" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5537022" refString="ScobleMHausmannAOnline list of valid and available names of the Geometridae of the Worldhttp://www.lepbarcoding.org/geometridae/species_checklists.php2019-11-01T00:00:00+02:00" year="2015">Scoble and Hausmann (2007)</bibRefCitation>
checklist, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lower" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Cerura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerura melanoglypta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanoglypta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Cerura melanoglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lower, 1905), is classified as a geometrine (
<bibRefCitation author="Oberthuer, C" journalOrPublisher="Etudes de Lepidopterologie Comparee" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536930" refString="OllerenshawJThe Global Lepidoptera Names Index (LepIndex).https://http://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/lepindex/detail/?taxonno=2463292019-10-29T00:00:00+02:00" year="1916">Ollerenshaw 2012</bibRefCitation>
), but has never formally been transferred from the notodontid genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Cerura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerura" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Cerura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schrank, 1802. We agree that this species should eventually be assigned to a genus in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
, but it is technically not in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
at this time.
</paragraph>
